import Foundation

var retirementGoals: [String: (String, String, String)] = ["Life Lessons" : ("Life is all about the experience. It is fleeting and really only meaningful on a very small scale-to you and those in your immediate surroundings. The best thing you can do with your life is to just go out and experience as much as possible. Have fun, find adventure, and maybe get a little blood on your face.","Gain 150 experience from ability cards.", "Open:90 (alt:83)"), "Dangerous Game" : ("You're no stranger to killing intelligent prey. Call it assassination if you must, but you just enjoy the hunt. And you enjoy collecting trophies of your kills. Which is why it is time to find new trophies up north. New types of Lurkers, giant, three-horned Algox, and fully operational machines! It's a treasure trove of dangerous challenges.", "Kill two Algox Guards, two Lurker Clawcrushers, and two Robotic Boltshooters", "Open: 44 (alt:88)"), "Aesther Outpost" : ("Frosthaven is not such an obscure place as it once was.It seems stories of the strange occurrences and fantastic creatures have reached far and wide, and there are certain parties interested in founding research outposts in the region, reasoning there is knowledge to be found. Now it's just up to you to do the leg work.","Immediately unlock A Strong Foundation (65) and follow it to a conclusion.", "Open: 44 (alt:88)"), "Team Building" : ("You are a people person. Sure, you've got a job to do, but would it hurt to make a few friends? Of course not. Nothing would make you happier than sitting around the hearth with some fast friends, drinking, talking, and playing games.","During eight different outpost phases, read a person's name in an event or section.", "Open: 85 (alt:21)"), "Build, not Destroy" : ("Sure, you've made a name for yourself as a seasoned fighter. When push comes to shove, you know how to kill a man. Still, it doesn't feel good. You long to find a new way of life. One that doesn't involve tearing something down, but rather building something up. To use your hands for a positive purpose: that would be ideal.","Experience theconstruction of twelve different buildings or building Upgrades",  "Open: 85 (alt:121)"), "Greed is Good" : ("There are many high and lofty goals in life-sick grandmas and epic love. Ridiculous. Only one thing matters and that's money--getting the most of it and keeping it safe.The weight of gold in your purse is a greater feeling than anything else imaginable, grandmas be damned.","Have 80+20xL gold in your possession, where L is the prosperity level.", "Open: 37 (alt:74)"), "Searching for the Oak" : ("Most people believe that the Great Oak in the capitol is the true face of the divine, but you have heard rumors of a great prophet who brought a sacred acorn from the north to plant the Great Oak. The true Oak is somewhere in this frozen waste, and you wish to gaze upon it in awe.","Personally loot 8 total lumber cards through loot tokens to unlock Sacred Soil 69 ), and then follow it to a conclusion.", "Open: 24, (alt:42)"), "The Study of Plants": ("Plants are infinitely more interesting than people. There are so many varieties, and each one has unique properties. If you could do nothing but look at new plants all day, you absolutely would. But you're running out of new plants to look at. Luckily there's an entirely new ecosystem in the northern part of the continent.","Personally collect five different types of herbs through loot tokens.", "Open: 24 (alt:42)"), "Merchant Class" : ("Merchants rule the world.Money is power, and you'd do anything get your hands on some. You figure if you can gather enough equipment together, you may be able to set up your own shop somewhere and work towards becoming a real merchant. Let the suckers keep fighting in dungeons over scraps.","Own 3 (helmet) items, 3 (chest) items, 3 (boot) items, 3 (1h) and/or (2h) items and 4 (potion) items.", "Open: 37 (alt:74)"), "Explore the Reaches" : ("Who are these people? The come all the way to this glorious wilderness and then huddle together in their drab, little buildings. It's madness.You will climb the tallest peak and go farther out into the snow plains and frozen seas than anyone else has done before. You will see the glorious sights yet unseen.","Complete five different scenarios that require (boat), (climbing) or (sled).", "Open: 90 (alt:83)")]


